   <category name='moves'>

      <section name='snail'>

         <para number='1' comment='In event on 205 - snail ride'>
         With a rumble, the snail starts moving. Hang on tight, you're in for an exciting ride!
         </para>

         <para number='2'>
         Squealing with excitement, you bounce up and down on the snail's back, waiting for it to pick up speed. It really is going very slowly. Oh well, maybe it just takes a while to get going. After all, it is a pretty large mollusc, and inertia must make it very hard to get that huge bulk started, but you are sure that once it gets moving it will just vroooooooooom along.
         </para>

         <para number='3'>
         The snail still hasn't sped up - in fact it is crawling along excrutiatingly slowly. You drum your heels against its shell and shout "Giddyup," but it seems to have no effect.
         </para>

         <para number='4'>
         Good grief! At this rate, it'll take all night just to get out of the field. The snail is moving at... well, at snail's pace. You decide to give up on this snail ride. Tutting in exasperation, you slide back down the side of the snail's shell and land on a large lettuce. You notice that the snail has moved all of two inches since you climbed on top of it. You can see just why snail racing never became popular.
         </para>

      </section>

